WEBVTT

00:05.890 --> 00:06.891
Now's the time.

00:10.174 --> 00:11.315
The time to build.

00:14.739 --> 00:16.460
Not everything that's built endures.

00:17.421 --> 00:19.223
Not everything that's built remains.

00:20.304 --> 00:21.806
Some things fall under pressure.

00:22.666 --> 00:24.228
Some things fade with time.

00:25.769 --> 00:27.691
Will what we build now endure?

00:29.773 --> 00:34.578
Will what we build speak through the next generation.

00:36.098 --> 00:39.844
We must be diligent, determined, and dedicated.

00:40.585 --> 00:45.091
After all, his church must be built to last.

00:47.195 --> 00:48.537
What have you believed that this morning?

00:49.638 --> 00:52.322
And then, God's not asking us to build a little sand castle.

00:52.422 --> 00:55.327
God's not asking us to build things with little flimsy.

00:55.347 --> 00:57.530
He's not even asking us to make a gingerbread house.

00:58.912 --> 01:00.895
Go on, have you know a gingerbread house doesn't last?

01:02.898 --> 01:05.682
But what God's asking us to do is make an investment.

01:06.338 --> 01:19.138
that surpasses us, that speaks into the next generation, that will continuously change eternity in the hearts and the lives of people.

01:19.860 --> 01:34.002
See, if we can invest in a generation now, that in turn will speak into the following generation, which will speak into the following generation, and you see this domino effect occur, and lives are continuously changed for God's glory.

01:34.530 --> 01:40.157
Many of you are here today because somebody spent time investing in you.

01:41.178 --> 01:43.681
Somebody spent time praying for you.

01:44.061 --> 01:52.251
Somebody spent time speaking into your life, pointing out the things that need fixed or even the things that you need to change in your life.

01:52.632 --> 01:56.757
Maybe you even had those people that encouraged you along the way.

01:57.057 --> 02:04.466
I don't know about your life, but I can think of countless people in different moments of my life that were

02:04.706 --> 02:14.823
that were really inspirational and helping me to be where I am today in my relationship with Christ and my leadership and my leading of the church.

02:15.103 --> 02:21.835
It's all due to people that spoke into my life, not yesterday, but generations ago.

02:22.836 --> 02:31.090
See, what we're building here at encountered church is not a temporary bandaid for a temporary fix.

02:31.394 --> 02:38.585
But what we're building here is his church that will be built to last.

02:39.406 --> 02:43.893
We're in week two of a series right now that we're simply calling built to last.

02:43.953 --> 02:52.445
And in this series, we're taking some time to not only look at the call that God set for us, we learned this last week, what did Jesus say?

02:52.465 --> 02:58.194
He says, I will build my church and the gates of hell will not prevail against it.

02:58.466 --> 03:02.733
will not conquer it, will not cause it to flutter if you would.

03:03.454 --> 03:07.260
But what God's calling us to do now is step into that assignment.

03:07.941 --> 03:13.870
Step into that calling and simply do the natural so that he can do the supernatural.

03:15.012 --> 03:23.665
I share with the worship team and some of the leaders before church is born as we gather together typically every Sunday morning just kind of get ourselves on the same page.

03:23.705 --> 03:26.610
And I share with them that if we as the church

03:26.690 --> 03:31.195
will do the natural, God will respond with the supernatural.

03:31.215 --> 03:31.936
How can I say that?

03:32.116 --> 03:37.521
Well, I see it numerous times occurring, not only in the Old Testament, but also in the New Testament.

03:37.541 --> 03:40.104
You see the day of Pentecost, they were gathered together.

03:40.144 --> 03:43.728
They were simply having a meeting and spending time in prayer.

03:44.028 --> 03:46.691
They were doing the natural side of things.

03:46.711 --> 03:47.832
They were being obedient.

03:47.892 --> 03:50.856
Jesus said, don't leave Jerusalem until the promise comes.

03:50.896 --> 03:53.138
They were meeting together

03:53.218 --> 03:55.260
praying, seeking the face of God.

03:55.460 --> 04:00.966
That's the natural, but in response, God showed up with a supernatural.

04:01.587 --> 04:19.066
We see in the Old Testament, time and time again, where people, the church, oftentimes, would gather together and do the natural, and God in response, would show up in a way that blew their minds, sometimes even pausing the service because his presence was so strong.

04:20.307 --> 04:23.090
I wonder today, what would happen

04:24.418 --> 04:31.987
If we, the body of Christ, would choose to do the natural to the best of our ability.

04:33.609 --> 04:37.154
See, a lot of times, oftentimes, we'll do the natural when it's convenient.

04:37.614 --> 04:38.495
Come on, somebody.

04:39.396 --> 04:41.599
We'll do the natural when it costs us nothing.

04:42.360 --> 04:44.322
We'll do the natural when it's easy.

04:45.184 --> 04:47.847
But I don't believe that's what God's calling is to do.

04:48.087 --> 04:50.450
Did you know building things is hard work?

04:51.138 --> 04:53.401
Come on, those of you in construction, give me a shout out.

04:53.682 --> 04:55.264
Building things is hard work.

04:56.206 --> 04:58.108
Man, I've learned that recently.

04:58.188 --> 05:01.253
I shared with you last week putting this flooring down man alive.

05:01.573 --> 05:02.575
That's hard work.

05:04.318 --> 05:18.438
But God's calling us to be willing to do even what's difficult so that His plan, His process, His desire is fulfilled.

05:19.420 --> 05:20.882
But He chooses to use

05:21.378 --> 05:21.839
You and me.

05:22.840 --> 05:23.841
Hey, let me introduce myself.

05:23.901 --> 05:24.982
My name is Pastor Chris.

05:25.203 --> 05:32.612
My wife and I have the honor and the privilege of leading what God's doing through encounter church here in Sedalia, in Warrensburg, in Lincoln.

05:32.852 --> 05:37.337
This morning we even have one of our very own speaking at another church nearby.

05:37.397 --> 05:41.262
So we are like, we are reaching the whole region for the cause of Christ.

05:41.302 --> 05:44.166
And I believe that's what God's called us as a church to do.

05:44.466 --> 05:46.889
If you're just joining us, you're checking things out.

05:47.229 --> 05:51.154
And we are honored that you're here as the girl said a while ago, welcome home.

05:51.714 --> 05:53.316
Maybe you're looking for a church home.

05:53.336 --> 05:54.618
I would say your search is over.

05:55.138 --> 05:56.360
You don't need to look any further.

05:56.660 --> 05:58.542
You have found a group of people that love you.

05:59.003 --> 06:05.130
Whether you're here in person or you're watching online, we are honored that you're with us this morning.

06:05.431 --> 06:08.174
Give us an opportunity to get to know you.

06:08.775 --> 06:09.876
Catch me in the lobby.

06:10.277 --> 06:11.438
Pause us just for a moment.

06:11.498 --> 06:18.066
You may have to tell me your name a few times over the course of a couple of weeks, but eventually it'll stick in this old nogget of mine.

06:18.567 --> 06:21.330
But I want to get to know you and build a relationship

06:21.474 --> 06:21.835
with you.

06:21.855 --> 06:25.321
Those of you that are online, again, help us get to know you as well.

06:25.622 --> 06:32.134
Give some shout outs, put some posts in that chat so we can make sure that we see that you were there this morning.

06:32.515 --> 06:32.716
All right.

06:32.736 --> 06:38.567
Well, last Sunday, we kicked off this series that we're simply calling built to last.

06:39.188 --> 06:42.354
And this series, what we're doing is we're simply

06:42.722 --> 06:44.725
giving God what he deserves.

06:44.765 --> 06:50.492
We're going and digging down deep, realizing that God's not looking for what's easy.

06:50.553 --> 06:53.116
God's looking for what's best.

06:53.156 --> 06:56.921
It's going to take intentionality on every one of our parts.

06:57.842 --> 06:59.765
What would happen at a job site?

06:59.785 --> 07:12.402
Those of you that are in construction this morning, what would happen on the job site if suddenly everybody was working hard, but you had a couple people on the sideline that were just kind of holding a shovel looking around.

07:13.794 --> 07:16.820
They probably wouldn't last very long, would they?

07:16.840 --> 07:21.670
They would probably have a conversation with their boss rather quickly.

07:21.930 --> 07:22.131
Why?

07:22.351 --> 07:24.515
Because everyone has to pull their weight.

07:24.776 --> 07:26.920
Everyone has to do the hard work.

07:26.960 --> 07:30.587
And I believe that's what God has for the church as well.

07:31.068 --> 07:31.669
Listen carefully.

07:32.050 --> 07:36.018
If we are not laying a foundation inside the church,

07:36.226 --> 07:45.855
than what we do outside these walls as we build a brand new building in just a couple of months, we'll have little to no effect on the culture around us.

07:46.916 --> 07:49.258
Come on, let me say that again, because that should have got a bigger response.

07:49.799 --> 08:05.554
If what we're doing in here, if we're not doing the hard work of building the foundation, if we're not doing the hard work of making ourselves available for the cause of Christ, if we're not being intentional in the process, then it doesn't matter what we build, it doesn't matter how

08:05.730 --> 08:14.682
Incredible the building is it will have little to no effect on the culture around us because inside the foundation will crumble.

08:15.724 --> 08:21.031
God's calling us to be a people of intentionality, a people of action.

08:21.111 --> 08:24.636
It's time, I believe, to build His church.

08:26.038 --> 08:31.265
We discovered last week that that's the theme that we're going to hold on to for this year.

08:31.585 --> 08:32.146
Build.

08:32.418 --> 08:33.019
his church.

08:33.079 --> 08:34.421
We're going to build it physically.

08:34.681 --> 08:36.084
We're going to build it spiritually.

08:36.304 --> 08:39.769
We're going to build that church relationally.

08:40.030 --> 08:43.215
We're going to do what it needs to be done because here's the reality.

08:43.535 --> 08:49.464
The church is not just an organization engaged in religious work.

08:49.484 --> 08:50.706
Come on, let that sink in.

08:51.970 --> 08:57.836
The church was not created to be an organization that's just engaged in religious work.

08:58.157 --> 09:03.963
It's a divine organism through which Jesus' life and power must operate.

09:04.724 --> 09:09.829
Jesus said, you will do even greater things than I have done.

09:11.511 --> 09:13.253
Wrap yourself around that.

09:14.794 --> 09:21.842
He said, Lazarus come out and this dude came hopping out of the tomb in his grave clothes.

09:22.370 --> 09:28.179
He spit in the mud, made a little bit of, spit in the dirt, made a little bit of mud, rubbing it on the guy's eye.

09:28.399 --> 09:31.704
And suddenly he could see, what?

09:31.724 --> 09:36.231
I'm not suggesting today that you go out and spit in the dirt and rub it on people.

09:36.271 --> 09:37.152
I'm not saying that.

09:39.256 --> 09:42.641
But Jesus said that we will do even greater things.

09:42.681 --> 09:43.502
How is that possible?

09:43.742 --> 09:48.149
Because we have the Holy Spirit moving in and through us.

09:49.531 --> 09:51.474
God has called us to be a people

09:51.618 --> 09:55.182
of action, of forward motion with Him.

09:55.422 --> 09:56.183
Here's what I know.

09:56.223 --> 10:04.792
If Jesus died for the lost world, then we must live to bring the world to Jesus.

10:05.713 --> 10:10.778
Again, if Jesus died for a lost world, and we believe that He died for this world, right?

10:11.078 --> 10:16.644
John 3 16, for God so loved the world that He sent Jesus, right?

10:17.004 --> 10:18.546
To die on a cross,

10:19.202 --> 10:23.627
that whoever believes in Him will not perish, will not die, but have everlasting life.

10:24.468 --> 10:32.436
Jesus, while we were still sinners, gave Himself on the cross of Calvary to give us hope, to give us a future.

10:32.576 --> 10:36.901
Jesus came to give us life and life more abundantly.

10:37.141 --> 10:45.970
If He came for that sole purpose, then how can we possibly sit on the sidelines, hold the shovel and go, huh?

10:49.474 --> 10:50.756
But can I be honest with you?

10:52.758 --> 10:55.381
I think for too many years, that's what the church has done.

10:57.464 --> 11:02.410
Well, praise God, I'll just go to church Sunday morning, hear the word of God.

11:02.530 --> 11:05.033
Hallelujah.

11:05.053 --> 11:05.393
Right?

11:06.795 --> 11:14.545
And then we leave church, we put our relationship with Jesus on the shelf and said, I'll catch you next Sunday morning.

11:14.565 --> 11:15.666
And we go about our week.

11:16.866 --> 11:21.414
I honestly believe that's why our culture is in the mess that it's in.

11:22.996 --> 11:30.910
The Bible says, if my people who are called by my name will humble themselves and pray and seek my face and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear from heaven.

11:31.531 --> 11:32.432
I will heal their lands.

11:32.593 --> 11:35.698
It doesn't say if the world will turn to me.

11:37.314 --> 11:49.207
But too often we use that scripture and say, oh, if America would just return to its roots, if America would just return to Jesus Christ, if America would once again be one nation under God, no, no, no, no.

11:49.427 --> 11:56.495
If the church... Oh, see, this must be inspiration for the Holy Spirit, because that's not even in my notes.

11:57.335 --> 11:59.818
And you guys are sitting there like you've never heard this stuff before.

12:01.220 --> 12:03.442
If my people, that's us.

12:04.642 --> 12:06.705
We'll humble ourselves and pray.

12:06.785 --> 12:08.427
Some of us need a little bit of humility.

12:09.729 --> 12:12.232
Come on, we got a little prideful.

12:12.252 --> 12:16.498
Oh, we got a little guilty of kind of shaking our fingers and people go, oh, I can't believe that you're doing that.

12:16.518 --> 12:18.661
Can you believe what Sally did yesterday?

12:19.342 --> 12:23.127
I saw it on their Facebook.

12:23.147 --> 12:30.657
I saw it on her Instagram, TikTok.

12:30.677 --> 12:34.322
Just for the record, I know it's TikTok, but TikTok's so much more fun to say.

12:35.202 --> 12:37.285
Some of you're like, did he really say tic-tac?

12:37.325 --> 12:37.605
Yeah.

12:38.186 --> 12:40.328
I say, dollar-gentral too, but it's okay.

12:42.731 --> 12:57.148
But we're so guilty of just shaking our finger, wagging that religious thought process at people that we lose sight that God's called us to be an extension of him to the world around us.

12:58.670 --> 13:01.874
God's called us to be a people that will reach the broken.

13:03.458 --> 13:05.221
Did you know it's not our job to fix them?

13:07.064 --> 13:08.045
It's our job to love them.

13:09.648 --> 13:10.429
Can I be honest?

13:10.469 --> 13:11.451
Sometimes that's hard.

13:13.113 --> 13:14.035
Stupid's hard to love.

13:18.842 --> 13:19.183
Right?

13:19.243 --> 13:21.266
Come on.

13:22.328 --> 13:23.169
It's hard to love.

13:24.992 --> 13:31.282
But nowhere in the Bible does it say love as God loves you unless they're stupid.

13:33.250 --> 13:35.293
Unless they're making dumb choices.

13:36.334 --> 13:38.577
Unless they continuously make mistakes.

13:40.359 --> 13:41.200
Can I be honest?

13:41.260 --> 13:43.503
Every one of us that continuously make mistakes.

13:44.805 --> 13:46.707
Though I have says none of us are perfect.

13:46.807 --> 13:47.568
Every one of us sin.

13:47.628 --> 13:50.392
Every one of us falls short of God's glorious standard.

13:51.313 --> 13:55.478
We're to love as God loves an unconditional love.

13:55.819 --> 13:59.163
Now does that mean that we accept wrong behavior?

14:00.865 --> 14:01.586
That's not love.

14:02.466 --> 14:04.208
accepting wrong behaviors, not love.

14:04.969 --> 14:06.070
But we should love them.

14:06.971 --> 14:08.572
The way that God loves us is this.

14:08.913 --> 14:13.317
He loves us so much that he refuses to allow us to stay the way we were.

14:15.900 --> 14:17.221
Oh, come on, that's good stuff right there.

14:18.583 --> 14:24.629
God loved you in the midst of your wrongdoing, but he loved you too much to leave you stuck in the mud.

14:25.650 --> 14:29.714
He's called you, the Bible says, out of the darkness and into the light.

14:30.530 --> 14:35.496
He's brought you out of despair into a life of hope and a future.

14:35.516 --> 14:41.803
In fact, he says in the Word of God, it says that I know the plans that I have for you, not destruction, not death, but hope in a future.

14:43.645 --> 14:51.654
That's the love that we are called by God's Word to offer up to those around us.

14:52.815 --> 14:55.538
That's how things are built to last.

14:55.842 --> 14:59.487
Again, I'm not talking about a fuzzy moment, lovey moment.

14:59.568 --> 15:00.970
Oh, I'm just in love.

15:02.292 --> 15:06.438
So if you guys remember junior high school, you were so in love, right?

15:06.638 --> 15:09.783
You remember that picture you used to carry around in your wall and guys with that girl?

15:09.843 --> 15:12.326
You're like, I'm in love with her.

15:12.747 --> 15:14.870
You've known her two days, but I'm in love with her.

15:17.234 --> 15:19.377
God's called us to a deeper love.

15:20.238 --> 15:22.802
God's called us to a deeper relationship

15:22.882 --> 15:38.552
with Him and the more that we get to know Him, the more that we love Him, the more that we spend time with Him, the more that we allow Him to pour into our lives, the more that His Spirit begins to rise up in us, the more that we begin to demonstrate Him to the world around us.

15:38.612 --> 15:41.938
We see this occurring in the early church in the book of Acts.

15:43.138 --> 15:46.042
Jesus has given his life on the cross.

15:46.102 --> 15:47.585
He was placed in the tomb.

15:47.645 --> 15:48.926
He rose from the grave.

15:48.947 --> 15:50.509
He ascended to heaven.

15:50.529 --> 15:55.376
He told the disciples, don't leave Jerusalem until the spirit comes or the promise comes.

15:55.676 --> 15:58.180
The Holy Spirit falls on the day of Pentecost.

15:58.521 --> 16:00.263
Church begins to erupt.

16:00.283 --> 16:06.212
Thousands are coming to know the Lord every day because of the cause of Christ, because of the move of the spirit.

16:06.412 --> 16:10.418
And now we have Acts chapter two, verse 42.

16:11.074 --> 16:13.797
It says all the believers, come on, say all.

16:15.258 --> 16:17.120
Look at your neighbor today and say that includes you.

16:17.160 --> 16:28.130
All the believers devoted themselves to the apostles teaching and a fellowship and to sharing them in meals, including the Lord's Supper and to prayer.

16:28.851 --> 16:34.876
A deep sense of all came over all of them and the apostles performed many miraculous signs and wonders.

16:35.357 --> 16:40.882
And all come on, look at your other neighbor, the second choice, the one you don't like quite as much and say all.

16:41.762 --> 16:46.569
And all of the believers met together in one place and shared everything they had.

16:46.630 --> 16:51.437
They sold their property and possessions and shared the money with those in need.

16:52.018 --> 17:00.912
They worshiped together at the temple each day, met in homes for the Lord's Supper, shared their meals with great joy and generosity.

17:01.573 --> 17:07.222
All the while, praising God, they were worshiping God and enjoying the goodwill of all the people.

17:07.502 --> 17:10.066
And each day, the Lord added to the church

17:10.594 --> 17:14.718
to their fellowship, those that were being saved.

17:15.980 --> 17:25.630
Now, last Sunday, we discussed chapter two, verse 42 briefly, but today I wanna use it as our launching pad to move us forward.

17:25.670 --> 17:25.930
Why?

17:26.251 --> 17:33.879
Because what we see as a response of their dedication is a church that truly began to flourish.

17:34.259 --> 17:40.466
Now, I don't know about you, but I never would encounter church just to be a church that exists.

17:41.826 --> 17:55.782
I never want us to be an organization that just gathers together to have a service, to hear an inspirational speech, to have a little bit of pre-speech entertainment that has some coffee in the lobby.

17:55.862 --> 18:01.389
I never want us to become guilty of just gathering because the building's open.

18:03.691 --> 18:09.618
My heart, my desire, God's word declares that we are to be a people with a cause.

18:10.210 --> 18:19.881
that we are to be a people responding in action, that we are to be a people that resemble and model what God has called us to do.

18:20.462 --> 18:24.166
And we see this in the dedication of the early church.

18:24.706 --> 18:33.837
Numerous times in the book of Acts, we read this statement, and the Lord added to the church, He added to the fellowship, those that were being saved.

18:34.237 --> 18:38.642
I don't know about you, but I believe that's building to last.

18:39.490 --> 18:42.333
That's what it means to build His church.

18:42.894 --> 18:47.839
They grew because they were connected to something larger than themselves.

18:49.080 --> 18:49.461
Come on.

18:50.442 --> 18:52.024
They were connected to God.

18:52.524 --> 18:54.426
They were connected to one another.

18:54.466 --> 18:56.829
They were connected to the mission.

18:57.049 --> 18:59.151
They were connected to the call.

18:59.612 --> 19:09.042
I said it last week, but I believe it warrants being said again, the days of church connectivity out of convenience must be behind us.

19:10.562 --> 19:12.404
Three of you agree with that, Hallelujah.

19:14.346 --> 19:21.332
It's time to pursue our relationship with God and connect Him with the church out of conviction for a greater calling.

19:23.634 --> 19:31.922
I wonder today, as we move from the blueprints to the construction site itself, I wonder, are you ready?

19:33.283 --> 19:36.046
Are you ready to say, Lord, I am all in?

19:37.147 --> 19:40.370
God, I'm ready to be your church.

19:40.578 --> 19:52.460
God, I'm ready to move forward with you because nothing that is built, not a house, not a church, not a family, not a ministry can possibly stand if the foundation is weak.

19:52.480 --> 19:58.271
Jesus tells us in our texts from last week that he would build his church.

19:59.454 --> 20:01.778
But now today he shows us how.

20:03.010 --> 20:10.618
He invites us into the process as we watch the foundation of the early church begin to grow from the ground up.

20:11.940 --> 20:16.565
After all, if the foundation is weak, again, the entire building will eventually collapse.

20:17.446 --> 20:19.949
We must build to last.

20:21.851 --> 20:27.777
I wanna, this morning I wanna give you four foundational pillars that we're gonna build upon.

20:27.897 --> 20:28.478
Are you ready for them?

20:29.079 --> 20:30.780
I wanna encourage you to take really good notes today.

20:30.800 --> 20:32.242
Number one is this.

20:32.322 --> 20:37.462
build on the unshakable, a church anchored in the Word.

20:37.502 --> 20:38.466
Now what do I mean by the Word?

20:38.486 --> 20:39.510
I'm talking about the Bible.

20:40.434 --> 20:42.642
We're going to build on the unshakable.

20:42.722 --> 20:45.968
We're gonna build upon the truth of God's Word.

20:46.228 --> 20:51.337
We don't just see this as a group of fancy stories, exciting moments.

20:51.598 --> 20:55.966
We don't see this as things we should just read or quote every now and again.

20:56.226 --> 21:00.594
We believe that the Word of God is the foundation that we will build upon.

21:00.614 --> 21:03.158
We're gonna talk about that in just a moment.

21:03.960 --> 21:05.202
I wanna challenge you.

21:05.858 --> 21:13.994
As we dive into this series, as we look at this idea of building his church, I want you to dig down deep this year.

21:15.056 --> 21:19.024
We're going to process through a lot of areas of the building process.

21:19.425 --> 21:24.274
I believe that God wants us to grab a hold of, and I want to encourage you, be apart.

21:24.546 --> 21:29.414
